'''''The New Jedi Order: Ylesia''''', part of the [[Star Wars: The New Jedi Order|New Jedi Order series]], is an [[eBook]] novella by [[Walter Jon Williams]], published in [[2002]] and set at the same time as Williams's novel ''[[The New Jedi Order: Destiny's Way]]'', in between chapter 21 and chapter 22 of the book.

Due to an oversight by [[LucasBooks]] and [[Del Rey]] that left many readers expecting the story to be included within the mass market paperback edition of ''Destiny's Way'', ''Ylesia'' was offered as a free download on [[StarWars.com]] on [[August 26]], [[2003]].<ref name="Error">{{SWArchive|url=eu/lit/novel/news20030826.html|text=''Ylesia'': Erratum and Recompense}}</ref>

==Publisher's summary==
'''RIPE FOR THE PLUCKING'''

''That's Jedi Knight Kyp Durron's opinion about the planet Ylesia, home base of the so-called Peace Brigade, a group of traitors dedicated to hindering the war efforts of the New Republic and hastening the ultimate victory of the merciless Yuuzhan Vong. Kyp's plan calls for a lightning-fast strike, backed with overwhelming force, to destroy the Brigade's offensive capabilities and teach prospective traitors that betrayal carries a heavy price. But young Jacen Solo, still bearing the scars of his imprisonment by the Yuuzhan Vong, has a better idea: a daring raid into the heart of Ylesia's capital, with the objective of capturing the Brigade's top leaders—-including the newly sworn-in President, Thrackan Sal-Solo, cousin to Jacen and his twin, Jaina''.

''But unknown to the Jedi and the New Republic forces, Supreme Overlord Shimrra of the Yuuzhan Vong has dispatched reinforcements to the Ylesia system. Instead of a swift surgical strike, Jaina, Jacen, Kyp, and their comrades are about to find themselves locked in a desperate battle for survival, with the odds stacked against them and time running out&hellip;.''

==Plot summary==
The [[Yuuzhan Vong]] assign [[Corellian/Legends|Corellian]] [[Governor-General/Legends|Governor-General]] [[Thrackan Sal-Solo]] to run the [[Peace Brigade]] out of [[Ylesia]]. The world becomes the target of a retaliatory strike by the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]], with a small [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] team including [[Darth Caedus|Jacen]] and [[Jaina Solo Fel|Jaina Solo]] landing first to liberate [[Prisoner/Legends|prisoners]]. The Jedi succeed and capture Sal-Solo and [[Senator/Legends|Senator]] [[Pwoe]], the erstwhile acting [[Chief of State (New Republic)/Legends|Chief of State]] of the New Republic, who shows his true colors as an enemy collaborator. The Jedi escape before the Yuuzhan Vong can rally their forces, thus breaking the back of the Peace Brigade movement. 

==Continuity==
This [[eBook]] was originally in the [[2003]] edition of [[The New Jedi Order: Destiny's Way|Destiny's Way]], but was left out due to an oversight. As recompense, [[Del Rey]] and [[LucasBooks]] made it available in August 2003 as a free ebook download on [[StarWars.com]]. It was later included as bonus content in the [[Dark Nest I: The Joiner King|''Joiner King'']] ([[2005]])<ref name="TERC" />

